The training of supervisors and enumerators hired to conduct 2019 national census is set to begin on July 15, the Kenya National Bureau of Statistics (KNBS) has announced. KNBS has recruited 2,700 ICT supervisors, 27,000 content supervisors and 135, 000 enumerators for the population count scheduled for the night of August 24-25. The ICT supervisors will train the content supervisors who will in turn train the enumerators for the digital census. The census will be paperless and the application has already been developed by local universities. "We have tested the programme and we are confident of its capacity to capture data," said KNBS Director-General Zachary Mwangi on Monday. More follows.  